MBOMBELA – An aviation accident occurred this afternoon just outside Nelspruit Airfield. Mbombela businessman Kerneels Kruger piloted the aircraft. The cause of the accident is not yet known.  Greg Wilcox from ER24 said the pilot was alone in the Cessna. It went down shortly after take-off, just off the runway and outside the airfield. He sustained minor injuries. “The aircraft was destroyed. He has a laceration on his head. He is stable.” Kerneels Kruger Kruger is being treated at Mediclinic Nelspruit and undergoing X-rays. The accident is to be investigated by the Civil Aviation Authority. Also read: BREAKING: R37 blocked by construction truck